  {
    "objectID": "index.html#interpretation",
    "href": "index.html#interpretation",
    "title": "Educational Attainment in Los Angeles County",
    "section": "Interpretation",
    "text": "Interpretation\nEducational attainment is not evenly distributed across local space. Some tracts show very high bachelor’s attainment, while others remain far below the county’s better-performing areas.\nThat matters economically because educational attainment is closely tied to labor-market opportunity, household income, and long-run regional inequality. A map like this can serve as a starting point for deeper work on local opportunity gaps, school quality, housing, and neighborhood stratification."
